I didn‚Äôt go home with the Golden Globe ~ but after the show I had the greatest dinner with my family that was filled with so much love and MANA as everyone around the table shared their hearts with their beautiful words and inspiring toasts
ü•Çü§é

After dinner and before dessert, I felt compelled to share a few words of my own - and show my family the note I was planning on pulling out of my pocket if my name was called and I was standing on that stage. 

It was a note written from my 10 year old daughter, Jazzy given to me that morning of the Globes. 

‚ÄúIf you can dream, you can do it.‚Äù

It‚Äôs the little things in life ~ like this note from my kid, or having my family all together like this that reminds me that I‚Äôve already won. 

That said‚Ä¶ 

One day, I hope to have the honor of my name being called, and standing on a stage, where I can pull this note out and read it to the world as our powerful reminder ~ 

If you can dream it, you can do it. 

Then I‚Äôll grab my family, we‚Äôll go drink tequila and stuff our faces with desserts all night long making a complete mess of ourselves. F*%# it üòÇü•Çüëäüèæ

And thank you ALL your INCREDIBLE & INSPIRING SUPPORT as I humbly journey down this long windy road. Thanks for having my back, as I‚Äôll always have yours. 

Onward and back to work.

Loved my sit down with these guys talking about my Smashing Machine journey and listening to their inspiring journeys as well. 

While none of us can relate to what it‚Äôs like being the ‚Äúgreatest fighter on the planet‚Äù ~ ALL of us can relate to the daily pressures that life puts on us and the expectations we put on ourselves as men. 

Chasing and achieving any level of greatness will always come with struggle and pain. It‚Äôs up to us to decide how it all affects us. 

Such a blast chopping it up with these guys, whom I have profound respect for as artists, but more importantly, they‚Äôre all great dudes.
